    "export_view": {
      "value": "<h2 id=\"Integrations:Revv/Rallio-WhatisRevv?\">What is Revv?</h2><p>Revv (powered by Rallio) engages customers with a simple survey automatically deployed after a closed transaction from RepairQ. The survey directs happy customers to provide a public review on local business review sites and encourages unsatisfied customers to share their concerns, privately, with you.</p><p>Revv integration looks for an SMS phone number (or, optionally, an email address) to contact the customer. In order for Revv to reach out to a customer via SMS on your behalf, there must be an\u00a0<strong>SMS Phone Number</strong> in their <a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1933312070/Managing+Customer+Profiles\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1933312070\" data-linked-resource-version=\"6\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Customer Profile</a> <strong>before</strong> the ticket is in Closed status.</p><p><strong>Note</strong>: Before following this tutorial, please visit <a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://www.rallio.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\"><strong>https://www.rallio.com</strong></a> to request a demo and sign up for an account. You will need your Auth Token and Rallio Location ID(s) before integrating with RepairQ.</p><h3 id=\"Integrations:Revv/Rallio-AdditionalResources\">Additional Resources</h3><ul><li><p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/plugins/servlet/servicedesk/customer/confluence/shim/spaces/SCD/pages/1933246465\" rel=\"nofollow\">Automated Notification Resources</a></p></li><li><p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/plugins/servlet/servicedesk/customer/confluence/shim/spaces/SCD/pages/1933803736\" rel=\"nofollow\">Sending an SMS Notification to a Customer</a></p></li><li><p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/plugins/servlet/servicedesk/customer/confluence/shim/spaces/SCD/pages/1933312070\" rel=\"nofollow\">Managing Customer Profiles</a></p></li><li><p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/portal/9/article/1933803609\" rel=\"nofollow\">Integrations: Twilio</a></p></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"680\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1932361859/Instructional%20-%200091cd.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"Integrations:Revv/Rallio-SettingupYourRevv/RallioIntegrationwithRepairQ\">Setting up Your Revv/Rallio Integration with RepairQ</h2><p /><p>Log into RepairQ as an Admin. On the Navigation Bar, go to <strong>Settings</strong> \u2192  <strong>Company Settings</strong>. On the Settings Overview page, click <strong>Integrations</strong> under the Account section.</p><p><strong>Note</strong>: The Revv Auth Token will be saved for all locations at the Company level, but individual accounts will be set up at the Location level.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1932361859/REVV%201.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1932361859/REVV%202.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>On the Integrations page, click <strong>Rallio</strong> from the Available Integration section.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1932361859/REVV%203.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>On the Rallio Integration screen, enter your Revv/Rallio Auth Token, then click <strong>Save REVV Settings</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1932361859/REVV%204.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"Integrations:Revv/Rallio-SettingUpRevvforYourLocation\">Setting Up Revv for Your Location</h2><p /><p>Log into the location where you want to set up Revv integration. On the Navigation Bar, go to <strong>Settings</strong> \u2192 <strong>Location Settings</strong>. On the Settings Overview page, click <strong>Integrations</strong> under the Account section.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1932361859/REVV%205.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1932361859/REVV%206.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>On the Integrations page, click <strong>Rallio</strong> from the Available Integration section. On the Rallio Integration screen, enter your Revv/Rallio Location ID and additional details, then click <strong>Save REVV Settings</strong>. Once you have saved the settings, the location is set up. You will need to repeat this process for any additional locations on your database.</p><p><strong>Note</strong>: Revv will send customer information after a ticket is in Closed status.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1932361859/REVV%209.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><ul><li><p><strong>Rallio Location ID</strong> - This is provided by REVV and is required for integration. This ID is specific to your location.</p></li><li><p><strong>Ticket Types</strong> - Select the Ticket Type(s) that you would like to send a survey.</p></li><li><p><strong>Ticket Resolutions</strong> - If using the <a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1932427638/Ticket+Properties+Require+a+Ticket+Resolution\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1932427638\" data-linked-resource-version=\"10\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Ticket Resolutions</a> feature, select any resolutions that will qualify the ticket for a survey. This field can be left blank.</p></li><li><p><strong>Service Authorizers</strong> - If using a Service Authorizer, select any specific provider(s) that will qualify the ticket for a survey. This field can be left blank.</p></li><li><p><strong>Service Programs</strong> - Select any specific Service Program(s) that will qualify the ticket for a survey. This field can be left blank.</p></li><li><p><strong>Enable REVV for this location</strong> - This will activate communication between RepairQ and REVV.</p></li><li><p><strong>Send customer email to REVV</strong> - By default, RepairQ will send over the SMS Phone from the <a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1933312070/Managing+Customer+Profiles\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1933312070\" data-linked-resource-version=\"6\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Customer Profile</a>. If this option is selected, it will also send over the customer's email information.</p></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1932361859/REVV%207.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p /><p>START 1.21.X</p>",
